
[1]slaver

   SLAV'ER, n. [the same as slabber.] Saliva driveling from the mouth.

   SLAV'ER, v.i.

   1. To suffer the spittle to issue from the mouth.

   2. To be besmeared with saliva.

    SLAV'ER, v.t. To smear with saliva issuing from the mouth; to defile
                                with drivel.
